verbose_text: One major difference is that the low-affinity proline transport systems in S. aureus are optimally activated at NaCl concentrations ranging from 0.75 to 1.0 mol/L [XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR], whereas the low-affinity proline transport systems in E. coli are inhibited by NaCl concentrations greater than 0.2 to 0.3 mol/L [XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR].
evidence: transport systems in E. coli are inhibited by NaCl
